description.p:
In order to solve the above problems, a kinematic support structure related to the present invention comprises a first support member, a second support member, a first ball, a second ball and a third ball;

the first support member comprises a first groove portion, a second groove portion and a third groove portion;

the second support member comprises a fourth groove portion, a fifth groove portion and a sixth groove portion;

the first ball, the second ball and the third ball are all movable with respect to the first support member and the second support member;

the first groove portion and the fourth groove portion face each other across the first ball;

the second groove portion and the fifth groove portion face each other across the second ball; and

the third groove portion and the sixth groove portion face each other across the third ball.

The first groove portion, the second groove portion and the third groove portion maybe arranged in a radial configuration;

the fourth groove portion, the fifth groove portion and the sixth groove portion may be arranged in a radial configuration;

the first groove portion may abut on the first ball in two points;

the second groove portion may abut on the second ball in two points;

the third groove portion may abut on the third ball in two points;

the fourth groove portion may abut on the first ball in two points;

the fifth groove portion may abut on the second ball in two points; and

the sixth groove portion may abut on the third ball in two points.

The travel ranges may have respective finite expanses;

the first ball holding structure (161, 180, 183) may comprise an elastic member for pushing the first ball in an inward direction of the first travel range;

the secondball holding structure (162, 180, 183) may comprise an elastic member for pushing the second ball in an inward direction of the second travel range; and

the third ball holding structure (163, 180, 183) may comprise an elastic member for pushing the third ball in an inward direction of the third travel range.

claim.claim-text:
A kinematic support structure (100), characterized in that:
the kinematic support structure (100) comprises a first support member (110), a second support member (120), a first ball (130), a second ball (140) and a third ball (150);
the first support member (110) comprises a first groove portion (111), a second groove portion (112) and a third groove portion (113) ;
the second support member (120) comprises a fourth groove portion (121), a fifth groove portion (122) and a sixth groove portion (123);
the first ball (130), the second ball (140) and the third ball (150) are all movable with respect to the first support member (110) and the second support member (120);
the first groove portion (111) and the fourth groove portion (121) face each other across the first ball (130);
the second groove portion (112) and the fifth groove portion (122) face each other across the second ball (140); and
the third groove portion (113) and the sixth groove portion (123) face each other across the third ball (150).

The kinematic support structure (100) as claimed in Claim 1, characterized in that:
the first groove portion (111), the second groove portion (112) and the third groove portion (113) are arranged in a radial configuration;
the fourth groove portion (121), the fifth groove portion (122) and the sixth groove portion (123) are arranged in a radial configuration;
the first groove portion (111) abuts on the first ball (130) in two points;
the second groove portion (112) abuts on the second ball (140) in two points;
the third groove portion (113) abuts on the third ball (150) in two points;
the fourth groove portion (121) abuts on the first ball (130) in two points;
the fifth groove portion (122) abuts on the second ball (140) in two points; and
the sixth groove portion (123) abuts on the third ball (150) in two points.

The kinematic support structure (100) as claimed in Claim 3, characterized in that:
the travel ranges have respective finite expanses;
the first ball holding structure (161, 180, 183) comprises an elastic member for pushing the first ball (130) in an inward direction of the first travel range;
the second ball holding structure (162, 180, 183) comprises an elastic member for pushing the second ball (140) in an inward direction of the second travel range; and
the third ball holding structure (163, 180, 183) comprises an elastic member for pushing the third ball (150) in an inward direction of the third travel range.
